year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joan Pittfield was born about 1634, in Honiton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Pitfield, was 26 and her mother, Agnes Payne, was 21. She married Richard Balster on 16 October 1662, in Exeter, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1634–":"umbes 1634–Surnud","1634–Female":"1634–Surnud","1638–1687":"1638–1687","–1698":"–1698","–Male":"Surnud","1640–1714":"1640–1714","1677–1768":"1677–1768","1609–1696":"1609–1696","1614–Female":"1614–Surnud","1634":"1634","1677":"1677","27 Jul 1629":"27. juuli 1629","1698":"1698","1687":"1687","1696":"1696","about 1677":"umbes 1677","1640":"1640","about 1634":"umbes 1634","1609":"1609","16 OCT 1662":"16. oktoober 1662","1638":"1638","1714":"1714","1614":"1614","1768":"1768","Exeter Saint Sidwell, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Exeter St Sidwell, Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Honiton, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Honiton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Honiton, Devon, England":"Honiton, Devon, England","Saint Peter Cathedral,Exeter,Devon,England":"Exeter, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1634–":"noin 1634–Kuollut","1634–Female":"1634–Kuollut","1638–1687":"1638–1687","–1698":"–1698","–Male":"Kuollut","164